WEBVTT

00:00.032 --> 00:02.601
<i>Previously</i> <i>on AMC's "Better Call Saul"...</i>

00:03.233 --> 00:05.566
What's our next move?
We gonna follow this guy?

00:05.668 --> 00:07.335
♪♪

00:07.437 --> 00:09.170
[Cellphone rings]

00:09.272 --> 00:10.938
Yeah.

00:11.040 --> 00:13.908
Jimmy: <i> Changed 1261 to 1216.</i>

00:14.010 --> 00:15.510
My brother broke the law.

00:15.612 --> 00:17.245
We can't just sit back and do nothing.

00:17.347 --> 00:18.412
Jimmy: It's my word against his!

00:18.515 --> 00:19.647
Jimmy, there's a tape.

00:19.749 --> 00:20.882
Ernie told me.

00:20.984 --> 00:21.883
♪♪

00:21.985 --> 00:24.385
For this, you destroyed our family?!

00:24.487 --> 00:26.554
Jimmy! That's enough!

00:26.656 --> 00:28.756
Chuck: You were a witness
to what happened here?

00:28.858 --> 00:29.957
I was.

00:33.562 --> 00:36.798
[Insects chirping]

00:36.833 --> 00:39.300
[Wind whistling]

00:41.000 --> 00:47.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:58.521 --> 01:02.123
[Engine rumbling]

01:07.397 --> 01:11.666
[Rumbling continues]

01:20.710 --> 01:24.245
[Rumbling continues]

01:44.901 --> 01:46.767
[Brakes squeal]

01:48.404 --> 01:51.505
[Air brakes hiss]

01:52.542 --> 01:57.078
[Rumbling continues]

02:14.464 --> 02:16.807
♪

02:26.808 --> 02:28.547
synced and corrected by oykubuyuk
www.addic7ed.com

02:29.584 --> 02:32.619
[Cellphone ringing]

02:45.478 --> 02:48.245
[Cellphone beeps]

02:48.281 --> 02:50.648
Yeah.

02:50.683 --> 02:54.085
Man: May I assume that you are armed?

02:54.120 --> 02:55.486
Yes.

02:55.521 --> 02:58.189
I do not wish to see your gun.

02:58.224 --> 02:59.590
And if I don't,

02:59.625 --> 03:02.259
I promise you won't see mine.

03:02.295 --> 03:04.261
Are we in agreement?

03:04.297 --> 03:06.497
We are.

03:06.532 --> 03:08.766
Expect two cars momentarily.

03:17.143 --> 03:18.542
[Vehicles approaching]

03:53.613 --> 03:55.513
[Engines shut off]

04:00.059 --> 04:01.759
[Vehicle door closes]

04:01.795 --> 04:03.861
[Insects chirping]

04:11.130 --> 04:14.499
[Paper rustling]

04:14.840 --> 04:17.974
You care to elaborate?

04:18.947 --> 04:24.117
It's not in my interest
for Hector Salamanca to die...

04:24.152 --> 04:25.952
at this time.

04:25.987 --> 04:27.520
Who is he to you?

04:27.556 --> 04:30.123
An associate of an associate.

04:30.158 --> 04:31.524
Mm.

04:31.560 --> 04:34.094
How very specific.

04:34.129 --> 04:36.763
Who is he to <i> you?</i>

04:37.833 --> 04:39.532
We had a disagreement.

04:39.568 --> 04:41.368
He threatened my family.

04:41.403 --> 04:43.536
I'm not gonna let that go.

04:43.572 --> 04:46.539
But you <i> had</i> let it go.

04:46.575 --> 04:48.775
You'd taken his money.

04:48.810 --> 04:51.611
Your family was no longer in danger.

04:51.646 --> 04:54.547
And yet, still, you robbed his truck.

04:54.583 --> 04:57.250
Shouldn't that have settled the matter?

04:57.285 --> 05:00.120
Most men would have walked away,

05:00.155 --> 05:02.155
but instead...

05:02.190 --> 05:06.559
you made an attempt on his life.

05:06.595 --> 05:08.328
Why?

05:12.033 --> 05:16.569
I understand that a civilian
found the driver

05:16.605 --> 05:19.806
after you robbed the truck.

05:20.842 --> 05:25.211
Hector murdered this civilian, correct?

05:32.320 --> 05:34.988
He wasn't in the game.

05:36.057 --> 05:39.292
I can't allow you to kill Hector.

05:39.327 --> 05:42.462
However, I am not completely
unsympathetic to your...

05:42.497 --> 05:44.864
sense of justice.

05:44.900 --> 05:48.701
You hurt Hector when you robbed that truck.

05:48.737 --> 05:51.004
You hurt his business,

05:51.039 --> 05:52.439
his pride.

05:52.474 --> 05:54.140
Quite effectively.

05:54.176 --> 05:59.212
And if you were to hurt him
in the same manner again,

05:59.247 --> 06:02.449
I would not stand in your way.

06:02.484 --> 06:05.452
You want me to rob another truck.

06:05.487 --> 06:08.221
If you feel so inclined.

06:08.256 --> 06:10.890
I'm done with that.

06:12.494 --> 06:15.228
Then our business here is finished.

06:15.263 --> 06:16.629
That's it?

06:16.665 --> 06:17.964
That's it.

06:17.999 --> 06:19.232
No more tracker,

06:19.267 --> 06:22.035
no more of your minions following me?

06:22.070 --> 06:23.837
Just like that?

06:23.872 --> 06:25.672
Just like that.

06:25.707 --> 06:27.240
Of course...

06:27.275 --> 06:31.578
I trust that you are done
with Hector Salamanca?

06:41.022 --> 06:43.590
[Breathes sharply]

06:43.625 --> 06:47.494
Goodbye, Mr. Ehrmantraut.

06:47.529 --> 06:50.430
Wait.

06:52.033 --> 06:55.068
You want his trucks hit

06:55.103 --> 06:58.838
because you want to disrupt his supply line.

06:58.874 --> 07:02.275
Hector's your competition.

07:02.310 --> 07:04.310
Why do you ask?

07:05.413 --> 07:09.082
Because I'm not done with Hector Salamanca.

07:09.117 --> 07:12.452
[Telephone ringing]

07:21.563 --> 07:23.096
[Telephone beeps]

07:23.131 --> 07:25.532
Offices of Jimmy McGill.
How may I help you today?

07:25.567 --> 07:27.967
- Jimmy: Hey. It's me.
- Oh, hey, Jimmy.

07:28.003 --> 07:31.905
Listen, um, something's come up,
and, uh, I need you

07:31.940 --> 07:34.541
to reschedule all
my appointments for tomorrow.

07:34.576 --> 07:35.909
Oh, okay.

07:35.944 --> 07:37.710
When do you want me to reschedule for?

07:37.746 --> 07:40.713
Let's talk about it tomorrow.

07:40.749 --> 07:41.948
Sure thing.

07:41.983 --> 07:44.050
Oh, and, uh, do me a favor...

07:44.085 --> 07:46.719
tell Kim I won't be back in tonight.

07:46.755 --> 07:48.187
Will do.

07:50.292 --> 07:53.960
Okay. That's it.

07:53.995 --> 07:55.495
Have a great night!

07:55.530 --> 07:57.497
- Mm.
- [Cellphone clicks]

08:00.669 --> 08:02.669
[Dog barking in distance]

08:08.677 --> 08:10.443
[Grunts]

08:10.478 --> 08:12.979
[Sniffling]

08:16.184 --> 08:18.284
[Match strikes]

08:24.793 --> 08:28.394
Chuck: You know you can wait inside.

08:29.731 --> 08:31.664
You won't want to hear it,

08:31.700 --> 08:33.633
but this is for the best.

08:35.804 --> 08:37.570
Please, Jimmy...

08:39.674 --> 08:41.341
Whatever you think of me,

08:41.376 --> 08:42.775
whatever colorful names

08:42.811 --> 08:45.645
you're calling me in your head right now,

08:45.680 --> 08:48.481
please understand I'm trying to help you.

08:48.516 --> 08:49.983
[Sighs]

08:50.018 --> 08:52.251
Here's what's going to happen.

08:53.355 --> 08:54.954
The police will arrest you,

08:54.990 --> 08:57.390
and I'm sorry,
but I will be pressing charges.

08:57.425 --> 09:00.193
I told you there would be consequences.

09:00.228 --> 09:02.629
But I [chuckling] have to believe

09:02.664 --> 09:04.964
that you'll face those consequences

09:05.000 --> 09:08.001
and you'll come out
the other side a better man.

09:08.036 --> 09:10.303
I know it's hard to see right now,

09:10.338 --> 09:12.672
but, Jimmy, this is an opportunity.

09:12.707 --> 09:14.540
That's why I'm doing this.

09:14.576 --> 09:15.808
Not to punish you.

09:15.844 --> 09:19.212
To show you, truly show you,

09:19.247 --> 09:23.750
that you have to make a change
before it's too late.

09:23.785 --> 09:26.753
Before you destroy yourself...

09:26.788 --> 09:28.354
or someone else.

09:28.390 --> 09:31.424
And I believe you <i> can</i> change.

09:31.459 --> 09:33.893
You'll find your path.

09:33.928 --> 09:35.995
And when you're ready,

09:36.031 --> 09:39.499
I will be there to help you walk that path.

09:39.534 --> 09:41.401
[Sighs]

09:43.204 --> 09:46.039
Here's what's gonna happen.

09:46.074 --> 09:50.043
One day, you're gonna get sick... again.

09:50.078 --> 09:52.845
One of your employees
is gonna find you curled up

09:52.881 --> 09:56.783
in that space blanket,
take you to the hospital,

09:56.818 --> 10:03.589
hook you up to those machines
that beep and whir and... hurt.

10:03.625 --> 10:06.626
And this time, it'll be too much.

10:06.661 --> 10:11.564
And you will... die there.

10:11.599 --> 10:13.099
Alone.

10:13.134 --> 10:17.103
[Vehicle approaches]

10:19.908 --> 10:22.975
There's my ride.

10:23.011 --> 10:24.644
♪ Hurry ♪

10:24.679 --> 10:25.978
[Police radio chatter]

10:26.014 --> 10:31.984
♪ Down ♪

10:32.020 --> 10:39.492
♪ Hurry down, sun ♪

10:39.527 --> 10:41.794
♪ Hurry down ♪

10:41.830 --> 10:43.463
Officer: Sir, I need
all your personal property,

10:43.498 --> 10:47.400
belts, ties, phone, rings, wallet.

10:47.435 --> 10:56.576
♪ I said, sun, won't you
hurry on, on down? ♪

10:56.611 --> 10:58.211
♪ Struggling ♪

10:58.246 --> 11:00.379
Need your socks and shoes
placed in that bag.

11:00.415 --> 11:02.181
[Vocalizing]

11:02.217 --> 11:04.450
♪ If someday my kids
are laughing together ♪

11:04.486 --> 11:06.619
Put these on your feet.

11:06.654 --> 11:10.456
♪ And having things that I never own ♪

11:10.492 --> 11:12.458
Turn to the right.

11:12.494 --> 11:14.761
♪ So bring on that new day ♪

11:14.796 --> 11:17.096
- [Flash bulb pops]
- Turn to the left.

11:17.132 --> 11:18.464
[Flash bulb charging]

11:18.500 --> 11:20.967
- [Flash bulb pops]
- Face me.

11:21.002 --> 11:22.368
- [Flash bulb pops]
- Left hand.

11:22.403 --> 11:25.338
♪ A great tomorrow is on its way ♪

11:25.373 --> 11:27.106
♪ Hurry, sundown ♪

11:27.142 --> 11:30.676
♪ Hurry down, sundown ♪

11:30.712 --> 11:32.712
♪ Hurry, sundown ♪

11:32.747 --> 11:34.614
♪ Hurry down, sundown ♪

11:34.649 --> 11:36.182
[Buzzer]

11:36.217 --> 11:39.552
- Right hand.
- Holy hell.

11:39.587 --> 11:42.522
I thought they were bullshitting me.

11:42.557 --> 11:44.891
- How the mighty have fallen.
- [Door clicks shut]

11:44.926 --> 11:47.326
- What the hell happened, man?
- [Buzzer]

11:47.362 --> 11:49.762
Nothing. Just family trouble.

11:49.798 --> 11:52.198
You're married?

11:52.233 --> 11:54.567
No. Disagreement with my brother.

11:54.602 --> 11:56.169
That hardass?

11:56.204 --> 11:57.403
I don't blame ya.

11:57.438 --> 11:59.172
So who you got representing you?

11:59.207 --> 12:01.174
I'll be representing myself.

12:01.209 --> 12:02.942
- Sign here.
- Moron.

12:02.977 --> 12:04.677
'Course, I knew that

12:04.712 --> 12:07.780
when you left that sweet Davis & Main gig.

12:07.816 --> 12:09.215
This way.

12:09.250 --> 12:10.616
Hey, speaking of...

12:10.652 --> 12:12.785
they, uh, still trying
to replace you over there?

12:12.821 --> 12:14.253
Arms out.

12:14.289 --> 12:16.556
How's, uh, Omar?

12:16.591 --> 12:18.491
Why? You looking to make a change?

12:18.526 --> 12:20.726
Well, leave all this glamour behind?

12:20.762 --> 12:22.261
Hey, who do you think's gonna catch this?

12:22.297 --> 12:24.130
Eh, it depends on who's
available when it comes in.

12:24.165 --> 12:25.965
- Face me.
- You think you might be available?

12:26.000 --> 12:27.600
Run your hands through your hair, please.

12:27.635 --> 12:30.254
Don't you wanna throw the book
at me for old times' sake?

12:31.105 --> 12:32.939
Mmm, I'll see if I can work some magic...

12:32.974 --> 12:35.408
but those decisions
are really above my paygrade.

12:35.443 --> 12:37.977
Oh, yeah? When did they
start paying you?

12:38.012 --> 12:40.980
- [Scoffs, chuckles]
- Sit here.

12:41.015 --> 12:43.282
- I gotta run, anyway.
- Left hand.

12:43.318 --> 12:45.418
Just had to see it for myself...

12:45.453 --> 12:46.986
[Handcuffs click]

12:47.021 --> 12:48.287
Jimmy McGill,

12:48.323 --> 12:50.423
getting fingerprinted with the hoi polloi.

12:50.458 --> 12:52.792
Well, I'm glad you enjoyed the show.

12:52.827 --> 12:54.493
[Sighs]

12:56.598 --> 12:57.964
I'll check and see

12:57.999 --> 12:59.632
if I can get your first appearance moved up.

12:59.667 --> 13:01.000
Thank you.

13:01.035 --> 13:02.501
It's pretty late.

13:02.537 --> 13:05.438
Chances are, you're spending the night.

13:05.473 --> 13:07.673
You, uh, gonna be okay?

13:07.709 --> 13:10.509
Beats the back of a nail salon.

13:10.545 --> 13:12.645
[Chuckles] I do not doubt that, my friend.

13:12.680 --> 13:15.648
[Chuckles]

13:15.683 --> 13:17.650
Oh, pick the biggest guy.

13:17.685 --> 13:19.652
Punch him as hard as you can, okay?

13:19.687 --> 13:20.920
Show dominance.

13:20.955 --> 13:23.022
Right. Got it. Dominance.

13:23.057 --> 13:25.992
You, uh, do know
how to throw a punch, right?

13:26.027 --> 13:28.294
Yeah, all right. Goodbye.

13:28.329 --> 13:31.130
[Chuckles]

13:31.165 --> 13:33.599
[Buzzer]

13:33.635 --> 13:37.436
[Lock clicks]

13:37.472 --> 13:39.338
[Door creaks]

13:39.374 --> 13:41.641
[Lock clicks]

13:44.993 --> 13:52.933
[Todd Terje's <i>"Alphonso Muskedunder"</i> plays]

13:55.771 --> 14:00.740
[Alarm beeping]

14:00.776 --> 14:02.809
[Music continues]

14:02.844 --> 14:04.444
♪

14:28.370 --> 14:30.870
[Scanner beeps]

14:30.906 --> 14:32.172
[Handle creaks]

14:32.207 --> 14:36.709
♪

14:36.745 --> 14:41.181
[Air rushing]

15:23.091 --> 15:24.657
Hey, Kim.

15:24.693 --> 15:26.392
Can I talk to you?

15:26.428 --> 15:27.660
Sure, Ernie.

15:27.696 --> 15:29.262
What's going on?

15:29.297 --> 15:32.298
Uh, Mr. McGill fired me.

15:33.502 --> 15:36.035
- Why? What happened?
- I don't...

15:37.139 --> 15:39.739
It doesn't matter.

15:39.774 --> 15:41.341
I just...

15:41.376 --> 15:43.510
Is Jimmy okay?

15:43.545 --> 15:45.345
I feel bad, like it's my fault.

15:45.380 --> 15:47.280
I didn't mean for this to happen.

15:47.315 --> 15:49.983
What happened to Jimmy?

15:50.018 --> 15:51.684
[Indistinct conversations]

15:51.720 --> 15:53.720
[Door closes in distance]

15:55.891 --> 15:59.192
[Footsteps approach]

16:00.516 --> 16:03.352
[Buzzer]

16:03.389 --> 16:06.256
[Keys jingling]

16:07.887 --> 16:11.388
- Man: McGill?
- Guard: Yeah.

16:12.958 --> 16:16.493
[Lock clicks, door creaks]

16:17.081 --> 16:20.382
You're up.

16:20.418 --> 16:23.385
[Handcuffs click, chains clinking]

16:23.421 --> 16:25.688
[Grunts]

16:29.861 --> 16:31.160
[Door creaks]

16:34.532 --> 16:40.302
Woman: We've got CR-2003113081.

16:41.706 --> 16:43.772
[Handcuffs click]

16:43.808 --> 16:45.274
James McGill.

16:45.309 --> 16:47.243
Yes, Your Honor. [clears throat]

16:47.278 --> 16:50.079
Not how I'm used to
seeing you in here, Mr. McGill.

16:50.114 --> 16:52.681
Not how I'd like to be seen.

16:52.717 --> 16:55.851
Well, you had quite the day yesterday.

16:55.887 --> 16:57.119
Okay.

16:57.155 --> 16:59.288
Mr. McGill, you've been accused

16:59.323 --> 17:01.323
of fourth degree felony
breaking and entering,

17:01.359 --> 17:02.858
which carries a maximum sentence

17:02.894 --> 17:05.861
of 18 months and a $5,000 fine.

17:05.896 --> 17:08.964
We've also got petty misdemeanor assault.

17:09.000 --> 17:12.701
Maximum six months' jail time
and a $500 fine.

17:12.737 --> 17:15.304
Plus, criminal damage to property,

17:15.339 --> 17:17.506
also misdemeanor with a maximum sentence

17:17.541 --> 17:19.675
of six months and a $500 fine.

17:19.710 --> 17:21.343
- [Door creaks]
- Victim is...

17:22.445 --> 17:24.512
Your brother Charles?

17:24.549 --> 17:25.814
Seriously?

17:26.884 --> 17:30.686
I assume you're prepared
to enter a plea at this time.

17:30.721 --> 17:32.188
Yes, Your Honor.

17:32.223 --> 17:34.523
I wish to enter a plea of not guilty.

17:35.726 --> 17:37.259
The court accepts

17:37.295 --> 17:39.295
and enters the defendant's plea
of not guilty.

17:39.330 --> 17:41.463
Now, Mr. McGill, have you secured counsel?

17:41.499 --> 17:42.698
Kim: Yes.

17:42.733 --> 17:44.300
Uh, Your Honor, Kim Wexler.

17:44.335 --> 17:46.135
I'll be representing Mr. McGill
in this matter.

17:46.170 --> 17:47.703
Judge: Just in time.

17:47.738 --> 17:49.505
Let's enter Ms. Wexler
as the attorney of record.

17:49.540 --> 17:53.542
Your Honor, if I may, um,
I'll be representing myself.

17:53.578 --> 17:56.879
I strongly advise against that, Mr. McGill.

17:56.914 --> 17:59.481
You know what they say about
a man who represents himself.

17:59.517 --> 18:01.116
Oh, I... I'm aware, but as you know,

18:01.152 --> 18:03.519
I've defended many people
in the criminal justice system.

18:03.554 --> 18:05.955
Your Honor, may I have a moment
to speak with my client?

18:05.990 --> 18:07.323
Sounds like he's <i> not</i> your client.

18:07.358 --> 18:09.558
[Sighs]

18:09.594 --> 18:10.960
[Sighs]

18:10.995 --> 18:12.628
Mr. McGill, would you like to take a moment

18:12.663 --> 18:15.331
to discuss this with your...
potential counsel?

18:17.401 --> 18:19.034
No, Your Honor. I'm all set.

18:19.070 --> 18:21.470
- I'm gonna represent myself.
- Your Honor...

18:21.505 --> 18:22.705
Not your client, Ms. Wexler.

18:22.740 --> 18:24.039
I'm sorry. I'm moving on.

18:24.075 --> 18:25.574
You two can work this out on your own time.

18:25.610 --> 18:26.976
I'm sorry. I was gonna call you,

18:27.011 --> 18:28.677
but then I thought I'd tell you in person.

18:28.713 --> 18:30.179
Mr. McGill.

18:30.214 --> 18:31.747
[Breathes sharply]

18:31.782 --> 18:34.350
So, on to the issue of bond.

18:34.385 --> 18:38.921
You have no priors
and no outstanding warrants.

18:38.956 --> 18:41.924
And where are you currently practicing law?

18:41.959 --> 18:44.193
I haven't seen you in my court in a while.

18:44.228 --> 18:45.761
Elder law.

18:45.796 --> 18:47.930
Judge: What a noble pursuit.

18:47.965 --> 18:50.366
One I hope you get back to very soon.

18:50.401 --> 18:52.501
Now, given your ties to the community,

18:52.536 --> 18:54.370
I see no reason to deny you bond,

18:54.405 --> 18:56.772
which I set now at $2,500.

18:56.807 --> 18:58.073
[Gavel taps]

18:59.644 --> 19:01.944
[Brakes squeal]

19:01.979 --> 19:06.015
[Car door opens]

19:06.050 --> 19:09.051
[Car door closes]

19:09.086 --> 19:10.286
[Engine rumbling]

19:25.269 --> 19:27.002
I fucked up.

19:32.643 --> 19:34.977
Chuck bamboozled me again.

19:35.012 --> 19:36.312
That tape?

19:36.347 --> 19:38.213
He made sure that Ernie heard it, right?

19:38.249 --> 19:39.815
Because he knew Ernie, bless him,

19:39.850 --> 19:41.984
would tell me about it and I would come over

19:42.019 --> 19:44.420
to try to destroy it
or steal it or whatever.

19:44.455 --> 19:45.654
Howard was there,

19:45.690 --> 19:47.756
and a P.I., if you can believe that,

19:47.792 --> 19:48.991
just waiting for me

19:49.026 --> 19:51.160
to lose my shit and bust in.

19:51.195 --> 19:53.429
Chuck played me like a fiddle!

19:53.464 --> 19:56.231
And schmuck that I am, I fell for it!

19:56.267 --> 19:58.634
Moron. [Breathes sharply]

19:58.669 --> 20:00.269
I'm sorry.

20:00.304 --> 20:01.837
And then, I didn't call you,

20:01.872 --> 20:04.006
which is stupid,
and I'm sorry about that, too.

20:04.041 --> 20:06.008
But I didn't call you for a reason, okay?

20:06.043 --> 20:08.243
'Cause this is <i> my</i> screw-up.

20:08.279 --> 20:09.845
I own it, okay?

20:09.880 --> 20:12.648
It's my responsibility to fix it.

20:12.683 --> 20:14.016
And I know you want to help.

20:14.051 --> 20:16.452
Of course you do, 'cause you're wonderful.

20:16.487 --> 20:20.255
But y-you're up to your ears in Mesa Verde.

20:20.291 --> 20:21.490
And I can't,

20:21.525 --> 20:24.259
I <i> won't</i> load this onto you, too.

20:24.295 --> 20:28.263
We have worked too hard
to let Chuck's bullshit vendetta

20:28.299 --> 20:30.466
threaten everything that we're building!

20:30.501 --> 20:33.035
I won't allow him to endanger our business!

20:33.070 --> 20:35.671
No! I will fix this.

20:35.706 --> 20:37.840
Myself. Me. Jimmy McGill.

20:37.875 --> 20:39.274
Okay?

20:39.310 --> 20:41.677
You have gotta let me do this on my own.

20:41.712 --> 20:43.078
[Sighs]

20:46.183 --> 20:50.319
Okay.

20:53.657 --> 20:55.824
Thank you. [Sniffles]

20:55.860 --> 20:57.493
[Footsteps depart]

20:57.528 --> 21:02.331
[Door opens, closes]

21:12.576 --> 21:15.344
I, uh, I finished it.

21:15.379 --> 21:19.715
I... I mean, I just touched up the edges.

21:19.750 --> 21:21.383
A little.

21:21.419 --> 21:24.720
Is... Is that okay?

21:24.755 --> 21:26.522
Oh.

21:26.557 --> 21:29.158
Uh, sure.

21:31.510 --> 21:35.078
It looks nice.

21:35.766 --> 21:38.500
You mind driving me to my car?

21:38.536 --> 21:40.369
Sure. No problem.

21:43.140 --> 21:45.407
Um, just so you know,

21:45.443 --> 21:49.044
this isn't a typical week around here.

21:49.079 --> 21:51.747
Yeah, [chuckling] totally.

21:51.782 --> 21:55.617
I... didn't think that it was.

21:55.653 --> 21:57.653
Ah.

22:03.461 --> 22:04.893
[Bell clinks]

22:04.929 --> 22:08.430
[Man speaking in Spanish on radio]

22:08.466 --> 22:11.733
[Woman coughing]

22:23.080 --> 22:24.279
_

22:24.315 --> 22:26.281
[Sighs] "Aaah!"

22:26.317 --> 22:28.617
_

22:28.652 --> 22:31.119
Ah.

22:31.155 --> 22:32.721
Mm-hmm.

22:32.756 --> 22:33.989
[Light clicks]

22:34.024 --> 22:36.124
_

22:37.428 --> 22:38.994
Mm.

22:39.029 --> 22:40.162
[Inhales sharply]

22:40.197 --> 22:43.632
_

22:44.370 --> 22:45.968
_

22:46.985 --> 22:49.867
_

22:56.113 --> 22:59.448
_

