23:31.148 --> 23:32.514
Mr. Clark?

23:32.550 --> 23:34.883
The doctor is ready.

23:39.890 --> 23:42.491
Doctor: And how may I
help you today, Mr. Clark?

23:42.526 --> 23:45.861
I believe our mutual
acquaintance called ahead.

23:45.896 --> 23:48.463
He told me what, but not how much.

23:48.499 --> 23:51.867
Mm. Well, I need a package...

23:51.902 --> 23:53.468
yea big.

23:53.504 --> 23:55.003
[Sighs]

23:55.039 --> 23:57.205
And what's that in grams?

23:58.275 --> 24:01.076
Unh. This big.

24:03.948 --> 24:05.514
[Bell clinks]

24:08.285 --> 24:10.052
[Bell clinks]

24:13.457 --> 24:17.726
[Chickens clucking]

24:26.637 --> 24:28.704
[Lock clicks]

24:32.309 --> 24:40.082
[Clucking continues]

24:47.438 --> 24:50.373
[Coffeemaker whirring]

24:58.350 --> 25:01.684
[Indistinct conversations]

25:15.554 --> 25:16.587
[Latches click]

25:16.622 --> 25:18.689
[Elevator bell dings]

25:18.724 --> 25:19.923
[Latch clicks]

25:34.307 --> 25:35.406
[Crunching]

25:35.441 --> 25:37.775
[Footsteps approach]

25:38.744 --> 25:40.444
Hey.

25:40.479 --> 25:42.446
Hey.

25:42.481 --> 25:44.848
Was somebody sitting here?

25:44.884 --> 25:46.483
No.

25:48.888 --> 25:51.088
[Sighs]

25:52.892 --> 25:54.358
So, how was it?

25:54.393 --> 25:55.726
How was what?

25:55.761 --> 25:58.662
[Crunching] Your night in MDC.

26:00.499 --> 26:02.399
I caught up with a few old clients.

26:02.435 --> 26:03.334
Yeah? [Chuckles]

26:03.351 --> 26:05.351
- Want one?
- Oh. [Chuckles]

26:06.788 --> 26:07.987
Yeah.

26:08.023 --> 26:09.622
This whole thing is a...

26:09.657 --> 26:10.890
big misunderstanding.

26:10.925 --> 26:12.258
Mm-hmm.

26:12.293 --> 26:14.160
There's absolutely no way
it's going to trial.

26:14.195 --> 26:16.429
Who wants <i> that</i> hassle? Not me.

26:16.464 --> 26:20.233
Whichever lucky soul at the
D.A.'s office catches this,

26:20.268 --> 26:22.168
looking at an easy clear.

26:22.203 --> 26:24.604
There's a felony in there, right?

26:24.639 --> 26:27.006
That would be a cla... Go ahead,

26:27.042 --> 26:29.175
classic case of overcharging.

26:29.210 --> 26:30.610
No offense.

26:30.645 --> 26:32.779
Happy to have a civil conversation,

26:32.814 --> 26:34.981
and I'm always ready to make a deal.

26:35.016 --> 26:37.183
- Just call me Monty Hall.
- [Chuckles]

26:37.218 --> 26:39.986
So you're looking to plea out
on this, then, Monty?

26:40.021 --> 26:42.021
If it's the right plea.

26:42.057 --> 26:44.590
I'm not perfect. Made mistakes.

26:44.626 --> 26:46.192
I'm willing to own up to them

26:46.227 --> 26:50.363
in a way that is satisfying
to both myself and the state.

26:50.398 --> 26:51.664
- Mm-hmm.
- Mm.

26:51.699 --> 26:54.500
Well, good luck with that.

26:54.536 --> 26:58.004
"Good luck with that" as in,
"I wish you well,"

26:58.039 --> 27:00.673
or, "I accept your challenge"?

27:00.708 --> 27:02.108
I wish you well.

27:02.143 --> 27:05.611
Play your cards right, they may go for it.

27:05.647 --> 27:07.613
"They"? Not you?

27:07.649 --> 27:09.282
Prosecuting <i> your</i> case?

27:09.317 --> 27:11.184
Nah, man. It's not me.

27:13.254 --> 27:16.456
You never catch a lucky break, do ya?

27:16.491 --> 27:19.192
- Bad timing?
- No, conflicted out.

27:19.227 --> 27:20.560
Conflicted out?

27:20.595 --> 27:22.295
I mean, I figured that'd happen.

27:22.330 --> 27:24.363
You and I have wheeled and dealed together

27:24.399 --> 27:25.998
too many times.

27:26.034 --> 27:27.900
There was no way the boss
was letting me run that one.

27:27.936 --> 27:29.035
[Crunching]

27:29.070 --> 27:30.636
It's not Ericsen, is it?

27:30.672 --> 27:32.738
The whole Albuquerque office is out.

27:32.774 --> 27:34.373
We all know you, Jimmy.

27:34.409 --> 27:35.575
- [Elevator bell dings]
- [Sniffles]

27:35.610 --> 27:37.577
Well, who is it? I don't know.

27:37.612 --> 27:40.246
They're pulling in someone from Belen.

27:40.281 --> 27:41.714
Um... Hay?

27:41.749 --> 27:45.051
Something Hay, I think.

27:45.086 --> 27:46.419
I don't know.

27:46.454 --> 27:48.221
Boss used the words "tough but fair."

27:48.256 --> 27:50.089
[Clears throat] Ahh.

27:50.125 --> 27:52.391
Gotta jam. [Chuckles]

27:52.427 --> 27:53.826
[Latch clicks]

27:53.862 --> 27:55.161
[Latches click]

27:55.196 --> 27:58.431
[Sniffles]

27:58.466 --> 28:00.299
Good luck.

28:04.105 --> 28:07.006
Burger's getting cold. [Chuckles]

28:07.041 --> 28:08.441
You want it?

28:08.476 --> 28:09.876
- Uh...
- Yeah?

28:09.911 --> 28:11.878
It has too many trans fats.

28:11.913 --> 28:13.112
Ohh!

28:13.148 --> 28:16.649
Those are the best fats.

28:19.754 --> 28:21.554
So they let you keep the car?

28:21.589 --> 28:22.889
- What?
- Davis & Main.

28:22.924 --> 28:26.893
They let you keep the, uh, German car?

28:26.928 --> 28:28.294
No.

28:28.329 --> 28:30.630
That blows.

28:30.665 --> 28:32.431
[Sighs]

28:59.861 --> 29:01.327
[Engine shuts off]

29:01.362 --> 29:03.329
[Insects chirping]

29:03.364 --> 29:07.934
[Wind whistling]

29:07.969 --> 29:11.537
[Keys jingling]

29:12.607 --> 29:16.175
[Lock disengages, trunk lid creaks]

29:23.151 --> 29:24.417
[Box thumps]

29:24.452 --> 29:26.819
[Chirping continues]

30:41.396 --> 30:42.628
[Shoes thump]

30:51.439 --> 30:56.075
[Power line creaking]

30:56.110 --> 31:01.280
[Engine rumbling]

31:02.784 --> 31:07.053
[Brakes squeal]

31:07.088 --> 31:08.487
[Engine shuts off]

31:17.598 --> 31:19.565
[Window creaks]

31:19.600 --> 31:21.267
Chuck: Ms. Hay?

31:21.302 --> 31:23.869
- Mr. McGill?
- Chuck, please.

31:23.905 --> 31:25.805
Meet me at the front door.

31:25.840 --> 31:28.040
Uh, they said to put my things
in the mailbox.

31:28.076 --> 31:30.343
Yes, please. Anything with a battery.

31:34.949 --> 31:36.315
[Clattering lightly]

31:36.351 --> 31:39.552
Did your brother <i> ever</i>
have a key to the house?

31:39.587 --> 31:42.054
Before the recent trouble, he did.

31:42.090 --> 31:45.491
He brought me my groceries and sundries.

31:45.526 --> 31:47.393
But we had a falling-out.

31:47.428 --> 31:50.129
I have an employee who does all that now.

31:50.164 --> 31:52.431
You took away your brother's key

31:52.467 --> 31:54.500
when you hired this employee?

31:54.535 --> 31:56.769
I changed the locks.

31:58.339 --> 32:00.506
Going... Going back to the confrontation,

32:00.541 --> 32:04.176
so I have it absolutely clear,
did he strike you?

32:04.212 --> 32:06.078
No, nothing like that.

32:06.114 --> 32:08.314
He backed me into a cabinet.

32:08.349 --> 32:09.582
Did he have a weapon?

32:09.617 --> 32:11.150
Well, as I mentioned,

32:11.185 --> 32:13.252
he used a fireplace poker
to break into my desk.

32:13.287 --> 32:15.187
But he never would have used it on <i> me.</i>

32:15.223 --> 32:17.223
Did you feel physically threatened?

32:18.326 --> 32:19.692
My brother is a lot of things,

32:19.727 --> 32:21.327
but even he has limits.

32:21.362 --> 32:23.929
And you're willing to appear as a witness

32:23.965 --> 32:26.132
even though he's family?

32:26.167 --> 32:27.933
Unfortunately, yes.

32:27.969 --> 32:30.035
If we continue with this,

32:30.071 --> 32:32.505
I'll need your sworn testimony.

32:32.540 --> 32:34.106
[Sighs]

32:34.142 --> 32:36.509
I've had situations
involving family members before

32:36.544 --> 32:39.945
where the injured party
has ultimately been reluctant

32:39.981 --> 32:41.714
to cooperate with my office.

32:41.749 --> 32:43.582
That won't happen.

32:45.686 --> 32:49.588
I'm curious about your strategy.

32:53.194 --> 32:55.361
Well...

32:55.396 --> 32:58.697
as officers of the court,

32:58.733 --> 33:01.734
I feel we should be held
to a higher standard.

33:01.769 --> 33:04.170
I don't intend to take it
easy on your brother

33:04.205 --> 33:05.671
just because he's a lawyer.

33:05.706 --> 33:06.906
Of course not.

33:06.941 --> 33:08.340
The bone of contention

33:08.376 --> 33:10.176
is going to be the felony
breaking and entering.

33:10.211 --> 33:12.745
Your brother's gonna want
to plead down to a misdemeanor,

33:12.780 --> 33:14.914
but I'll hold the line on the felony.

33:14.949 --> 33:16.248
[Clears throat]

33:16.284 --> 33:18.717
Which means this could possibly go to trial.

33:18.753 --> 33:19.985
[Sighs]

33:20.021 --> 33:22.388
Now, I... I want to be mindful

33:22.423 --> 33:24.590
of your comfort and well-being.

33:24.625 --> 33:26.392
With, with your condition,

33:26.427 --> 33:28.227
are you able to appear before the court?

33:28.262 --> 33:29.829
In person?

33:29.864 --> 33:32.064
I certainly appreciate you
accommodating me today

33:32.099 --> 33:33.666
by coming here,

33:33.701 --> 33:36.202
but don't worry,
I'm able to tolerate being out

33:36.237 --> 33:38.404
for short periods
with a few minor adjustments.

33:38.439 --> 33:41.307
Nothing that will
overly inconvenience the court.

33:42.910 --> 33:44.810
I'll get started on this.

33:48.082 --> 33:51.050
Unless you have other concerns.

33:51.085 --> 33:53.219
I just...

33:53.254 --> 33:56.455
I just keep thinking.

33:58.459 --> 34:00.793
[Voice breaking] You know,
Jimmy has a good heart.

34:00.828 --> 34:02.194
I'm, I'm sure he does.

34:02.230 --> 34:03.963
It's not an excuse for what he's done.

34:03.998 --> 34:07.299
[Sighs] But he's my brother.

34:07.335 --> 34:11.036
[Stuttering] And I know... well, he...

34:11.072 --> 34:13.304
well, he's emotional.
He flies off the handle.

34:13.341 --> 34:14.639
I understand,

34:14.675 --> 34:15.908
but this is more than flying off the handle.

34:15.943 --> 34:18.377
I'm not going to defend his actions.

34:18.411 --> 34:20.045
But I can't help wondering

34:20.081 --> 34:22.648
if there's not a better solution.

34:22.683 --> 34:24.049
For everyone.

34:24.085 --> 34:27.018
[Clock ticking]

34:36.492 --> 34:38.592
[Insects chirping]

34:44.318 --> 34:47.585
[Wind rushing]

34:52.641 --> 34:55.341
[Bird cawing]

35:23.463 --> 35:26.931
[Engine rumbling]

35:49.081 --> 35:53.150
[Gun clicks]

36:05.201 --> 36:07.869
[Brakes squeal]

36:07.904 --> 36:09.037
[Air brakes hiss]

36:09.072 --> 36:10.538
[Engine shuts off]

36:15.295 --> 36:17.528
[Truck door closes]

36:53.528 --> 36:57.163
[Gunshot]

36:58.600 --> 37:01.801
[Bullet clinks]

37:09.321 --> 37:10.687
[Gunshot]

37:16.580 --> 37:17.972
_

37:18.662 --> 37:19.624
_

37:19.668 --> 37:23.070
[Gunshot]

37:26.201 --> 37:27.603
_

